1
00:00:01,466 --> 00:00:04,133
MC: I've arrived at Basement Level 2.

2
00:00:04,133 --> 00:00:06,866
In the darkness, the scent of decay spreads around. I struggle to carry the lantern down the stairs and cautiously press the black box in my hand.

3
00:00:06,866 --> 00:00:10,500
It's as if there's an invisible flame in the air, making it hard for me to breathe. My skin also feels a faint burning pain.

4
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:18,266
??(Lucien): [talking through the transmitter] It took 36 minutes longer than expected. How is your physical condition now?

5
00:00:18,266 --> 00:00:23,066
MC: A bit hot and stuffy... my whole body still feels a bit sore.

6
00:00:23,066 --> 00:00:26,866
??(Lucien): Is the pain severe?

7
00:00:26,866 --> 00:00:30,933
MC: It's okay. I can still bear it.

8
00:00:30,933 --> 00:00:37,033
I enunciate each word slowly. After a moment of silence, I hear the other person speak again.

9
00:00:37,033 --> 00:00:40,133
??(Lucien): Then let's continue.

10
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:46,833
??(Lucien): In front of you is a corridor. The path should be relatively smooth.

11
00:00:46,833 --> 00:00:57,766
??(Lucien): Follow the stairs to the left and try to see if you can open the third room. There should be a cabinet inside.

12
00:00:57,766 --> 00:01:00,400
Per his instructions, I successfully feel my way to the room he mentioned and even luckily push the door open directly.

13
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:04,066
As I enter the room, I am greeted by a wave of dust that has been undisturbed for a long time. Torn and tattered papers lie scattered across the floor, their contents illegible.

14
00:01:04,066 --> 00:01:07,366
I brush away the moldy air in front of me; the room is even larger than I imagined, and after feeling around for a long time, I finally see a huge cabinet.

15
00:01:07,366 --> 00:01:10,566
The rusty cabinet door is already a bit twisted. When I finally pry it open, I find neatly stacked thick notebooks.

16
00:01:10,566 --> 00:01:12,933
I curiously pull out a book. The pages are already yellowed, but the text remains clear.

17
00:01:12,933 --> 00:01:15,666
MC: In 1973... the 19th experimental report on the 'Simulation of Radiation from the 1917 Comet'...

18
00:01:15,666 --> 00:01:18,266
MC: In 1995... the 42nd experimental report on the 'Evol Energy Core'...

19
00:01:18,266 --> 00:01:21,633
Various complex numbers and figures are recorded sequentially according to time. I browse through them blankly, completely unable to understand what they mean.

20
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:25,100
??(Lucien): Is this lady encountering some trouble?

21
00:01:25,100 --> 00:01:27,466
MC: Not really. However, this cabinet is more extensive than I imagined, and there is a lot of information inside.

22
00:01:27,466 --> 00:01:29,000
MC: It feels like I can't take everything out at once.

23
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:37,266
??(Lucien): It's okay. Each booklet should have a numerical label. Let's start with the important ones first.

24
00:01:37,266 --> 00:01:38,966
As he speaks, he reports a few numbers.

25
00:01:38,966 --> 00:01:41,400
MC: ...1974, 1981, 1995... Alright, I've got them all.

26
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:43,533
MC: By the way, I just found many tables in the room I passed by.

27
00:01:43,533 --> 00:01:46,366
MC: There are lots and lots of pressable and rotatable... buttons? There are also some mysterious shapes on the wall that I can't quite understand.

28
00:01:46,366 --> 00:01:47,900
MC: Do you know what they are?

29
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:49,900
The person opposite the black box also seems stunned and falls silent.

30
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:57,900
??(Lucien): Is that table slightly curved, and are the structures on the wall mainly dot-shaped and block-shaped?

31
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,166
MC: That's right!

32
00:01:59,166 --> 00:02:05,866
??(Lucien): [chuckles then sighs] I didn't expect... such things would still be left behind.

33
00:02:05,866 --> 00:02:08,200
He seems to smile as he lets out a long sigh, with a particular indescribable itch to try.

34
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:16,066
??(Lucien): Today's gains have completely exceeded expectations. Thank you for your hard work. Let's get ready to return.

35
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:18,900
I walk alone through the ruins corroded by decay.

36
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:22,433
I thought I had long been accustomed to facing the scent of death, but when I see a familiar yet blurry figure in the desolation, my steps involuntarily quicken.

37
00:02:22,433 --> 00:02:25,933
As the sharp alarm sounds, his figure becomes increasingly clear.

38
00:02:25,933 --> 00:02:27,966
I stand still from a distance, looking back at that smile-filled gaze.

39
00:02:27,966 --> 00:02:30,400
MC: [happily] Lucien, why are you here again! Didn't I tell you to wait for me in the safe house?

40
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:39,400
Lucien: I wanted to go for a walk, but as I walked farther, I felt a bit scared being alone. It would be more reassuring to have someone accompany me.

41
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:43,466
Lucien: I'm very happy to have waited for you.

42
00:02:43,466 --> 00:02:45,800
I know this is just his excuse, but I am equally happy not to expose him.

43
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:48,366
I skillfully put on the isolation*** suit Lucien specially made for me not far away and walked up to him.

44
00:02:48,366 --> 00:02:50,733
MC: A certain someone really pushes their luck, making one person do multiple tasks. Not only do I have to help with research, but I also have to run errands.

45
00:02:50,733 --> 00:02:57,066
Lucien: They are indeed pushing their luck, so I suggest you ask for more compensation from him.

46
00:02:57,066 --> 00:02:59,466
MC: [smiles softly] Then I will make him help me deal with all kinds of troubles.

47
00:02:59,466 --> 00:03:04,200
Lucien: I think... he would be more than willing to do such things.

48
00:03:05,866 --> 00:03:07,533
As we chat casually and leisurely, the safe house appears before us.

49
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:12,400
I habitually walk into the house, descend the stairs, pass through layers of iron doors, and remove my isolation suit in front of the last iron door.

50
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:15,800
As the door closes, a dazzling light suddenly pierces through the darkness.

51
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:18,266
I fall into a momentary daze, vaguely hearing distant and cold voices.

52
00:03:18,266 --> 00:03:20,333
??(Not Lucien, distant voice from the past): "Increase the dosage... the data is showing significant fluctuations…"

53
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:22,666
A sense of phantom pain surges through my entire body as if a black tide is rolling in.

54
00:03:22,666 --> 00:03:24,133
Lucien: MC.

55
00:03:24,133 --> 00:03:25,933
Lucien's voice comes through the speaker.

56
00:03:25,933 --> 00:03:30,933
Lucien: Our experiment No. 0625 is about to start. Are you ready?

57
00:03:30,933 --> 00:03:32,966
I take a deep breath and lift my head with a determined gaze.

58
00:03:32,966 --> 00:03:34,300
MC: I'm ready.

59
00:03:44,033 --> 00:03:46,933
Today's experiment doesn't seem to yield any results.

60
00:03:46,933 --> 00:03:51,066
I secretly observed his calm face and silently drew a conclusion in my mind.

61
00:03:51,066 --> 00:03:56,333
Upon careful reflection, I realize that in the past six months, I have hardly ever seen any signs of frustration on Lucien's face, nor has he ever caused me as much pain as those madmen from the past.

62
00:03:56,333 --> 00:04:00,633
Therefore, although I cannot fully trust researchers like him, I can still achieve long-term cooperation with him.

63
00:04:00,633 --> 00:04:04,700
Lucien quickly organizes today's data and then opens another set of records and a map.

64
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:13,800
Lucien: Yesterday's radiation tide has intensified the radiation in Zone X. The personnel in these areas need to be relocated soon.

65
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:19,633
MC: [worriedly] ...The heavily contaminated radiation zone is getting larger and larger. Will the entire Zone X eventually be…

66
00:04:19,633 --> 00:04:27,333
Lucien: There is such a trend, but the changes in the world always exceed our imagination.

67
00:04:27,333 --> 00:04:35,200
Lucien: Many areas in Zone X are still only mildly contaminated, so there's no need to be too pessimistic yet.

68
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:39,366
Facing my worries, he gives a reassuring smile.

69
00:04:39,366 --> 00:04:44,166
Lucien: However, time is indeed running a bit tight.

70
00:04:44,166 --> 00:04:48,433
MC: [worriedly] Do you want to move to a safer place first?

71
00:04:48,433 --> 00:04:56,900
Lucien: My research on the books and materials in this building is not yet finished, and the equipment and samples are also here.

72
00:04:56,900 --> 00:05:03,166
MC: ...Are these things more important than human beings?

73
00:05:03,166 --> 00:05:08,566
Lucien doesn't answer me. He just smiles, puts on the protective gear, and picks up the organized boxes.

74
00:05:08,566 --> 00:05:12,633
Lucien: Let's go. Let's take a look at the city.

75
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:18,900
The city's ruins have been eroded by rain, snow, and frost, leaving only moss and weeds freely spreading throughout.

76
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:25,300
The world wears down this desolate land in different ways, but it has never listened to everyone's prayers and pleas.

77
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:32,700
Lucien and I skillfully turn into an alley, pass through an almost completely unshielded door, and see a weak middle-aged man inside the dilapidated house.

78
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:36,333
Lucien: How are you doing today?

79
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:40,900
Middle-aged man: ...Doctor, you're here... my whole body still hurts... but I feel much better…

80
00:05:40,900 --> 00:05:49,800
Lucien: Don't worry, that's the normal effect of the medication. You'll feel more comfortable tomorrow.

81
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:56,300
As Lucien speaks, he injects medication into the middle-aged man's arm and hands him a packet of medicine.

82
00:05:56,300 --> 00:06:02,100
Lucien: Just like I told you before, once a day.

83
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:06,500
Middle-aged Man: Alright... Thank you very much…

84
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:12,933
Lucien develops all those medications himself. I don't know how he manages to create these in such a ruined world, but he somehow does.

85
00:06:12,933 --> 00:06:18,333
It's as enigmatic as 'radiation'.

86
00:06:18,333 --> 00:06:25,500
No one knew what it was before; everyone only knew that approaching certain places would cause inexplicable pain and death.

87
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:32,033
Some called it a 'curse', some called it a 'colorless beast', and others said such places were 'God's slaughterhouse'.

88
00:06:32,033 --> 00:06:38,400
Even though I had been with it for many years, no one ever told me what it really was.

89
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:45,966
I will always remember when I saw Lucien again after we had agreed to work together; he took out a notebook and started drawing for me.

90
00:06:45,966 --> 00:06:57,400
Lucien: It is called 'radiation.' It is the form of energy that moves as waves or subatomic particles, radiating outward in straight lines from the radiation source in all directions.

91
00:06:57,400 --> 00:07:05,600
Lucien: Based on its energy level and ability to ionize substances, we generally classify it as 'ionizing radiation' and 'non-ionizing radiation.'

92
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:10,733
MC: ...I don't understand. Why does it make people die?

93
00:07:10,733 --> 00:07:18,033
Lucien: You can temporarily imagine it as countless bullets, too small for you to see, being shot at you.

94
00:07:18,033 --> 00:07:29,400
Lucien: They break everything inside your body, preventing your blood from regenerating and your heart from continuing to beat.

95
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:34,066
Lucien told me that this is 'knowledge'.

96
00:07:34,066 --> 00:07:39,900
MC: If I still want to ask 'why', is that also an effect of 'radiation'?

97
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:44,400
His smile deepened, and in those deep, mysterious eyes, I seemed to see countless emotions that I couldn't understand.

98
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:48,533
Lucien: This is 'curiosity'.

99
00:07:48,533 --> 00:07:58,166
Lucien: It has nothing to do with 'radiation'. It belongs only to you and is the first step towards the world and yourself.

100
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:02,966
After noting down some things, Lucien takes me to meet many people.

101
00:08:02,966 --> 00:08:08,566
They are either weak or healthy; some undergo drastic changes overnight, while others are lucky enough to regain their vitality.

102
00:08:08,566 --> 00:08:15,133
I never understood why there were still people in the contaminated areas. Despite fearing death, they still chose to set foot on this gloomy land.

103
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:19,133
Later, following Lucien, I gradually understood that there are always many people in this world.

104
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:28,766
There will always be those with nowhere to go, those who yearn for death, those at their wit's end, those longing to return to their hometown, and those who refuse to believe.

105
00:08:28,766 --> 00:08:37,133
And Lucien… he records and treats each of them according to their situations. Seeing their admiring gazes, I silently avert my eyes.

106
00:08:38,633 --> 00:08:47,033
Man: City Lord... I beg you... please kill... me…!

107
00:08:47,033 --> 00:08:56,200
In the last visited hut, blood and pus soak through the tattered sheets. Their entire body is rotting, leaving only a grotesque face that still faintly resembles a human being.

108
00:08:56,200 --> 00:09:02,700
People call such individuals 'living corpses'. They seem to be alive but are also dying.

109
00:09:02,700 --> 00:09:06,833
Lucien: You have already done very well.

110
00:09:06,833 --> 00:09:13,566
Lucien: We still have opportunities, and you will undoubtedly have many possibilities.

111
00:09:13,566 --> 00:09:20,433
Lucien's calm voice is particularly eerie amidst the wailing as he gently comforts the person and changes the bandages covering him.

112
00:09:20,433 --> 00:09:27,266
The clear liquid flows through the needle into the vein, while the glowing instrument continuously shines. Lucien observes and records simultaneously.

113
00:09:27,266 --> 00:09:35,266
The man's pleas and wails seem to be separated from him by some barrier. He just smiles and injects another dose of medication.

114
00:09:35,266 --> 00:09:44,700
Lucien: Only by living can you reach the future. Your life is still very important.

115
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:50,666
As we step out of the building amid the wailing, the gentle and brilliant light shines down as always, but I feel incredibly cold.

116
00:09:50,666 --> 00:09:53,766
A little child runs over with a tattered book and stands beside Lucien.

117
00:09:53,766 --> 00:09:56,233
Little Boy: Teacher, how should this character be pronounced?

118
00:09:56,233 --> 00:10:00,133
Lucien: Let me take a look.

119
00:10:00,133 --> 00:10:04,166
He squats down, looks at the spot the little boy is pointing to, and teaches him word by word.

120
00:10:04,166 --> 00:10:06,933
Suddenly, the wailing behind us stops.

121
00:10:06,933 --> 00:10:11,500
I instinctively turn my head, but the glaring sunlight blurs my vision.

122
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:16,700
Lucien: Is the dosage still not right…

123
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:21,133
Faintly, Lucien's voice seems to come through.

124
00:10:22,533 --> 00:10:27,933
When I turn to the side again, I see him with his hand on his chin, lost in thought, then he continues talking to the child.

125
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:34,500
I gaze at him deeply, feeling that sometimes this man has a kind of calmness that is terrifying.

126
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:42,166
On the way back, I remain silent. When death arrives, it always easily strips me of all words and emotions.

127
00:10:42,166 --> 00:10:47,500
Lucien: MC, are you feeling sad?

128
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:54,766
Lucien's question shatters the silence. I ponder it for a long moment, then nod slowly.

129
00:10:54,766 --> 00:11:02,966
Lucien: [sighs then speaks] Do you think death is the end?

130
00:11:02,966 --> 00:11:09,933
I don't know why he would ask this. Looking at the blood-red dusk outside the window, many faces that I have only seen once and never again flash through my mind.

131
00:11:09,933 --> 00:11:15,700
MC: When a person dies, they are just dead, and there is nothing left.

132
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:27,266
More and more people are becoming seriously ill, and the radiation alarm in the safe house is sounding more intensely every day. However, Lucien still has no plans to move.

133
00:11:27,266 --> 00:11:33,433
Seeing him inject medication into himself more frequently, I finally break the silence.

134
00:11:33,433 --> 00:11:37,666
MC: Are you okay?

135
00:11:37,666 --> 00:11:45,900
Lucien: Don't worry. This body has been confirmed to be able to last for some time in this environment.

136
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:50,000
MC: ...Don't you feel any pain?

137
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:59,766
Lucien: I'm not very sensitive to pain, so it won't be a factor in my judgment.

138
00:11:59,766 --> 00:12:06,000
His tone is relaxed, and he even curls up on the sofa to read the pile of documents I retrieved for him earlier.

139
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:10,566
Despite trusting Lucien's judgment, I still faintly feel a certain sense of urgency.

140
00:12:10,566 --> 00:12:16,100
MC: Lucien, will our experiment really yield results?

141
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:22,166
MC: In such a harsh world, shouldn't we lower our high expectations? Wouldn't it be better to just be ordinary people?

142
00:12:22,166 --> 00:12:31,133
Instead of chasing for answers that we may never get in our lifetime, wouldn't it be enough to just simply live?

143
00:12:31,133 --> 00:12:36,366
For a long time after that, Lucien doesn't say anything.

144
00:12:36,366 --> 00:12:43,233
He just gazes at me quietly, his bottomless eyes like an abyss, making it hard to see clearly.

145
00:12:43,233 --> 00:12:47,500
Lucien: I don't know.

146
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:57,733
Lucien: But experiments inevitably come with failures and contingencies, so I can't give you a definite answer.

147
00:12:57,733 --> 00:13:02,966
Lucien: But I believe there will be results.

148
00:13:02,966 --> 00:13:09,800
Even knowing that he might fail, he will definitely keep trying—until he reaches a point where he can no longer move forward, and then calmly starts over from the beginning.

149
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:17,400
Lucien: For this, I am willing to pay any price.

150
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:21,833
At night, I have a dream.

151
00:13:21,833 --> 00:13:27,566
In the dream, those severely ill people stand up, the desolate land starts to have flowers, and there are more smiling faces.

152
00:13:27,566 --> 00:13:35,200
However, everything shatters like broken glass the next moment, revealing a dreadful and bewildering void.

153
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:42,366
Lucien: MC, we have failed. This world will not get better.

154
00:13:42,366 --> 00:13:48,700
Lucien, standing in front of me, starts to rot and blur, eventually turning into an exploded mess of blood.

155
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:53,800
I can feel the cold liquid seeping through my body, flowing over my cheeks and arms.

156
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:58,366
Lucien: MC, how do you feel now?

157
00:13:58,366 --> 00:14:04,700
I can't see Lucien's face, but I can hear his voice filling my mind.

158
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:11,400
I feel him gently embrace me, patiently waiting for my answer as usual.

159
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:17,500
The incredibly realistic sensation makes it hard for me to tell whether this is a dream or reality.

160
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:24,400
Lucien: Listen to the voice in your heart and tell me your answer.

161
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:29,000
I feel my entire body start to tremble violently, and countless unfamiliar images flash through my mind.

162
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:32,733
I see Lucien's calm yet mad eyes;

163
00:14:32,733 --> 00:14:37,433
I hear the sharp whirring sound of a machine;

164
00:14:37,433 --> 00:14:42,366
I see blood pouring like a waterfall, drenching my entire body like rain.

165
00:14:44,233 --> 00:14:49,566
I scream and open my eyes—only to see Lucien's face the next second.

166
00:14:49,566 --> 00:14:57,066
The face in front of me overlaps with the one in my dream, but he only has a worried expression on his face; some kind of familiar scent clings to his body.

167
00:14:57,066 --> 00:15:00,300
Lucien: Are you okay?

168
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:05,233
I'm tongue-tied and can only stare at him blankly.

169
00:15:05,233 --> 00:15:12,533
I don't know if it's the effect of the moonlight, but his entire figure seems to be covered with a faint halo, which then dissipates in the blink of an eye.

170
00:15:12,533 --> 00:15:17,366
MC: I… seem to have had a nightmare and seen many scenes.

171
00:15:17,366 --> 00:15:23,366
He gently strokes my back, but his eyes imperceptibly darken a little.

172
00:15:23,366 --> 00:15:33,366
Lucien: I observed that your Evol fluctuations are quite significant. The recent radiation tide may have also affected you.

173
00:15:33,366 --> 00:15:39,933
Perhaps it's the lingering effect of my dream, but as I look at Lucien standing before me, I feel an inexplicable timidity and uneasiness. I subconsciously reach out my hand to him.

174
00:15:39,933 --> 00:15:45,833
Suddenly, I realize my body is without an isolation suit, and Lucien has almost no protective equipment. I quickly wrap myself in the blanket.

175
00:15:47,366 --> 00:15:52,300
MC: Lucien, get away from me quickly! I'm not wearing an isolation suit! Get out quickly!

176
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:55,100
Lucien: ….

177
00:15:55,100 --> 00:16:04,133
Lucien: A certain lady's decision is too hasty, making me a bit worried that you might actually dislike me.

178
00:16:04,133 --> 00:16:09,633
The next second, a warm palm covers my head through the blanket.

179
00:16:09,633 --> 00:16:16,233
I can't see Lucien's expression at this moment.

180
00:16:16,233 --> 00:16:23,300
It seems to be a time that belongs solely to him. As long as he doesn't allow it, I can't enter.

181
00:16:23,300 --> 00:16:30,733
Even long after, I still don't know what expression he had during that nearly minute-long silence.

182
00:16:30,733 --> 00:16:37,533
In the end, Lucien walks out of the room without a word.

183
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:44,166
As I lie on the bed, my heart is still pounding with lingering fear, and I have lost the desire to fall asleep again.

184
00:16:44,166 --> 00:16:52,500
The inexplicably familiar scent floods the entire room, making me sit up in frustration and can't help but sigh.

185
00:16:52,500 --> 00:17:00,200
In the faint moonlight, I suddenly see some small, scattered black spots 'growing' on the floor.

186
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:02,866
Curious, I squat down and find that it is very fresh, with a faint hint of a metallic smell—

187
00:17:02,866 --> 00:17:05,800
It's blood!

188
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:14,600
Cold sweat instantly seeps out of my back. Only Lucien had been here just now... Could he be injured? Or affected by the radiation?!

189
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:21,500
I hastily don the isolation suit and run in the direction of the bloodstains.

190
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:29,400
The intermittent and scattered bloodstains seem to *guide* me, leading me step by step toward an unfamiliar corridor.

191
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:33,900
??: “Rrrrr…”

192
00:17:33,900 --> 00:17:40,466
A strange and piercing sound echoes from the depths, like... the sound I heard amidst the chaotic scenes.

193
00:17:40,466 --> 00:17:45,800
Faint specks of light flicker faintly in the darkness, and I suddenly feel a surge of fear and foreboding —

194
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:50,366
That glimmer of light might destroy many things, but I can't stop my footsteps.

195
00:17:50,366 --> 00:17:56,000
I traverse through numerous unfamiliar corridors and finally step into the glimmer of light—

196
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:59,166
A vast yet desolate building appears before me, with an enormous pit at its center.

197
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:03,166
Gazing down, I see the pit divided into numerous sections by plastic sheeting. The walls and sheeting are splattered with varying shades of crimson.

198
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:09,133
I descend into the pit, pushing aside the hanging curtains as if unveiling the true face of another world.

199
00:18:09,133 --> 00:18:12,600
A thick stench of blood fills my nostrils, and the grating whirring of machinery churns my entire brain.

200
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:17,333
A familiar figure flickers past in a corner cubicle.

201
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:23,500
The curtain blurs his face, and the shadow gracefully raises a machine, lowering his arm like a conductor.

202
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:28,033
The transparent shower curtain is covered with dense 'raindrops'. Something is sliced open and falls heavily.

203
00:18:28,033 --> 00:18:33,233
It rolls on the ground, spinning endlessly, before finally stopping in the gap between the curtains.

204
00:18:33,233 --> 00:18:38,233
I see a person's face, the same face that was wailing and begging for death.

205
00:18:38,233 --> 00:18:43,433
Now, he lies silently on the ground, his rotting eyes staring rigidly at me.

206
00:18:43,433 --> 00:18:48,966
And in the next second, the shadow picks him up, revealing that familiar face through the gap.

207
00:18:48,966 --> 00:18:55,800
Standing against the light, he turns his head, his calm yet crazed eyes gleaming brightly.

208
00:18:55,800 --> 00:19:00,700
He doesn't seem surprised by my arrival.

209
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:05,200
An arm shrouded in the shadows casually slashes, slicing the entire curtain open in an instant-

210
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:11,666
-revealing the full, blood-soaked figure of Lucien before my eyes.

211
00:19:11,666 --> 00:19:18,166
My rapid breathing fogs up the transparent visor on my isolation suit, obscuring most of my vision, yet I've never seen him more clearly.

212
00:19:18,166 --> 00:19:21,100
I burst into a sprint.

213
00:19:21,100 --> 00:19:24,166
A torrent of images and distant memories flooded my mind, slicing through me like a scalpel.

214
00:19:24,166 --> 00:19:29,233
??: ...That’s a highly-contaminated area, and you say that child came out alive?!

215
00:19:29,233 --> 00:19:33,000
??: She is crucial to our experiment. We need to study her powers—we have no choice!

216
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:36,133
Under the glaring lights, someone binds me to an iron table.

217
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:39,866
Countless days and nights blur together as flames sear my skin and sharp blades inflict ceaseless pain.

218
00:19:39,866 --> 00:19:44,066
??: ...Under high radiation, her body remains stable... she's carrying high-intensity energy... 5 people died from…

219
00:19:44,066 --> 00:19:48,166
??: Evol core… like a quasi-magnetic field…

220
00:19:48,166 --> 00:19:52,666
Strangers speak in tongues I cannot comprehend, their eyes perpetually fixed on the distant future, but all I sense is madness.

221
00:19:52,666 --> 00:19:57,833
They are all lunatics, lunatics of the apocalypse, and I only want to escape.

222
00:19:57,833 --> 00:20:02,733
As I blast open the laboratory door, a gentle-faced young boy appears before me in the thick smoke.

223
00:20:02,733 --> 00:20:07,866
Boy: Once you pass through this door, you can run free.

224
00:20:07,866 --> 00:20:11,800
He pressed a button, and accompanied by a piercing siren, an iron door not far away slowly opened.

225
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:16,666
Boy: Remember to take the forest path. Nothing will harm you there.

226
00:20:16,666 --> 00:20:21,000
For a moment, I thought this would be another experimental trap set by those lunatics.

227
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:25,300
The hurried footsteps gradually came closer, but the boy made no move to jump away. He simply watched me patiently.

228
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:32,833
Boy: You have three minutes to decide whether you want to be caught by them again or trust me.

229
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:39,500
Boy: Of course, you can also trust your instincts.

230
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:44,533
Those deep, dark eyes seemed to possess a strange power. In an instant, I turned and ran towards the door.

231
00:20:44,533 --> 00:20:50,900
Suddenly, another thought struck me, and I turned back at the iron door.

232
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:54,833
MC: Why are you helping me?

233
00:20:54,833 --> 00:21:00,966
Boy: If you want to know who you are one day, you can come find me.

234
00:21:00,966 --> 00:21:05,233
MC: ….How can I find you?

235
00:21:05,233 --> 00:21:11,533
Boy: I will let you find me. Remember to learn how to protect yourself.

236
00:21:12,833 --> 00:21:17,766
Years later, I remembered his words when I finally realized the 'Grim Reaper' I carried within me.

237
00:21:17,766 --> 00:21:23,566
I want to know who I am and what I want to change.

238
00:21:23,566 --> 00:21:29,566
And he seemed to know that I would eventually return to this 'land of death,' leaving messages and marks in each area ravaged by radiation-

239
00:21:29,566 --> 00:21:34,500
I thought Lucien was different.

240
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:38,633
Maybe he was hiding it too well, or perhaps he finally lost his patience.

241
00:21:39,966 --> 00:21:44,166
The grating sounds of machinery and footsteps seemed to follow me like a shadow, yanking my taut consciousness back to reality.

242
00:21:44,166 --> 00:21:47,866
As if anticipating my arrival, many places were already locked up.

243
00:21:47,866 --> 00:21:52,600
The ground and walls around me tremble slightly, permeated with a strange yet familiar power that makes me feel dizzy.

244
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:58,000
The unbearable heat and dizziness slow my steps, but the chilling footsteps keep my nerves on edge.

245
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:02,233
To speed up, I simply take off the isolation suit.

246
00:22:02,233 --> 00:22:05,000
I don't want to die, I must live on.

247
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:09,766
My heart feels like it's burning, urging me not to stop moving.

248
00:22:11,366 --> 00:22:14,466
After escaping aimlessly, I found myself back in that deep pit again.

249
00:22:14,466 --> 00:22:20,433
As I gaze upon the blood-stained black bags concealed behind the curtain, a sudden idea strikes me.

250
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:24,833
Shrouded in the humid darkness, I dare not make a single move.

251
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:30,433
The already cramped space seems to be devouring the last vestiges of air, causing me to slow my breathing instinctively.

252
00:22:30,433 --> 00:22:37,500
Muffled rustling sounds intermittently pierce the silence, sounding eerily ominous in the heightened state of my hearing.

253
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:42,233
I force myself to focus, but the image of those eyes keeps intruding into my mind uncontrollably.

254
00:22:42,233 --> 00:22:46,933
….The truth is, I don't know Lucien at all.

255
00:22:46,933 --> 00:22:51,400
Is it because he has never fully revealed himself to me, or have I never truly gotten close to him?

256
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:56,100
Amidst a tinge of sadness, I realize that none of this matters now—I must focus on how to survive.

257
00:22:56,100 --> 00:23:01,233
I exhale softly, and a familiar surge of power gathers in my chest. Through the haze, I catch glimpses of fragmented images —

258
00:23:01,233 --> 00:23:07,966
The hum of machinery fills my ears, while the pulsing red light and constantly fluctuating curves leave afterimages on my retina.

259
00:23:07,966 --> 00:23:12,233
I walk through the crowd of people, and flowers bloom by the roadside.

260
00:23:12,233 --> 00:23:17,400
In that hazy world, there exists a pair of eyes that always gaze upon me with unwavering clarity.

261
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:25,800
Sharp, resolute, and scrutinizing. He seems to be peering through me to a distant place.

262
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:28,800
MC: …Lucien.

263
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:33,133
I part my dry lips but make no sound.

264
00:23:33,133 --> 00:23:38,766
The air seems to thin even further, and in a daze, I feel as if I've been transported back to countless moments of frigid breathlessness in the past.

265
00:23:38,766 --> 00:23:44,500
The unknown and fear tug at my remaining consciousness as if I'm about to be swallowed by the boundless darkness.

266
00:23:44,500 --> 00:23:49,066
I don't know how much time has passed; the rustling sounds around me have also disappeared.

267
00:23:49,066 --> 00:23:53,766
Perhaps Lucien has gone somewhere else to find me. Thinking this, I carefully unzip the zipper.

268
00:23:54,633 --> 00:23:57,566
Before I even adjust to the harsh white light, I crash straight into Lucien's gaze.

269
00:23:57,566 --> 00:23:59,733
The world roars, and my heart seems to stop for a moment.

270
00:23:59,733 --> 00:24:03,800
Lucien: [chuckles] Not hiding anymore?

271
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:06,166
He squinted his eyes and chuckled softly.

272
00:24:06,166 --> 00:24:08,700
He crouches in front of me, his hair scattered across his forehead, damp with water droplets, his exposed chest rising and falling slightly.

273
00:24:08,700 --> 00:24:11,333
He casually grips the chainsaw and pulls the starter cord with one hand, producing a piercing and terrifying sound.

274
00:24:11,333 --> 00:24:13,500
I can't fathom how long he's been waiting like this.

275
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:17,033
Five minutes? Ten minutes? Or has he been silently observing my every move from the beginning, watching me run continuously and then return here, lying down in the bag?

276
00:24:17,033 --> 00:24:19,900
Fear makes me clench my fingers tightly, but I do not avoid his gaze, trying to find the answers I seek in his eyes.

277
00:24:19,900 --> 00:24:21,833
MC: ...Why did you help me escape back then?

278
00:24:21,833 --> 00:24:25,033
I don't answer him; instead, I ask a question I have never figured out. As if slightly surprised, Lucien's eyes flicker.

279
00:24:25,033 --> 00:24:29,133
Lucien: Because I worry that they will damage my test subject.

280
00:24:29,133 --> 00:24:31,666
He answers directly and calmly as if it's the most natural answer.

281
00:24:31,666 --> 00:24:35,533
Somehow, I suddenly don't feel afraid at all. I even feel like laughing, so I simply pull at the corners of my mouth and lie in the bag.

282
00:24:35,533 --> 00:24:39,033
I don't want to think about whether his close proximity will be affected by the radiation from my body, nor do I want to consider how to escape from this rapidly moving saw.

283
00:24:39,033 --> 00:24:42,266
Maybe I've always wanted to find some way to talk to Lucien.

284
00:24:42,266 --> 00:24:45,200
MC: Then why do you want to study me?

285
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:49,133
MC: Why do so many people want to study me? Do you want to change the world?

286
00:24:49,133 --> 00:24:52,933
Lucien: [chuckles] Change the world?

287
00:24:52,933 --> 00:24:56,166
Lucien laughs as if what I just said is a joke.

288
00:24:56,166 --> 00:25:00,600
But soon he restrains his laugh, his gaze turns slightly bright as he looks at me again, and his voice carries an undisguised seriousness and stubbornness.

289
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:07,300
Lucien: Why change the world? I think this world is fine.

290
00:25:07,300 --> 00:25:14,133
Lucien: What I want to seek is 'evolution'.

291
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:30,866
Lucien: Radiation, disasters, and the like are merely puzzles posed by objective reality, and we are the problem solvers.

292
00:25:30,866 --> 00:25:37,433
Lucien: Only in this way do we qualify to step onto a new level.

293
00:25:37,433 --> 00:25:42,000
His voice is exceptionally gentle, accompanied by the buzzing sound of an electric current that sends shivers down my spine.

294
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:46,100
MC: ...Are you going to kill me?

295
00:25:46,100 --> 00:25:50,333
Lucien: [chuckles] Do you want me to?

296
00:25:50,333 --> 00:25:55,333
He lowers the machine in his hand, bringing the rapidly spinning chainsaw blade dangerously close to my neck.

297
00:25:55,333 --> 00:26:03,333
Lucien: I can dismember your limbs, but that won’t be particularly useful to me right now.

298
00:26:03,333 --> 00:26:18,200
Lucien: I can extract your brain intact and keep it active for a certain period of time. Maybe you would still be considered 'alive' in some biological sense.

299
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:31,933
Lucien: Of course, the most important thing is your heart and... your Evol 'core'.

300
00:26:31,933 --> 00:26:45,066
Lucien: I've been curious for a long time about how it works, allowing you to withstand any severe radiation threat and survive until now.

301
00:26:45,066 --> 00:26:56,366
Lucien: Maybe when I cut you open, there will be an answer to all this. What do you think?

302
00:26:56,366 --> 00:27:02,000
I can feel the intense wind pressure from the chainsaw pressing down on all my nerves, but at the same time, it seems that an even more majestic and surging force is roaring in my chest.

303
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:05,533
My mind is almost blank, leaving only some kind of instinct.

304
00:27:05,533 --> 00:27:08,633
MC: ....No, you are wrong.

305
00:27:08,633 --> 00:27:12,400
MC: If I die, you won't get any answers.

306
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:16,866
At this moment, I seem to see something more clearly.

307
00:27:16,866 --> 00:27:25,033
MC: And... it's not you who is studying me to carry out so-called 'evolution', but rather me using you to complete ‘change’.

308
00:27:25,033 --> 00:27:30,266
The corners of his mouth curve into a more pronounced arc.

309
00:27:30,266 --> 00:27:41,133
Lucien: Is that so? But it seems I have the opportunity to lock you up again at any time.

310
00:27:41,133 --> 00:27:55,233
Lucien: I have many ways to keep you from going anywhere, even... to take away your right to choose death.

311
00:27:55,233 --> 00:28:01,800
MC: Then go ahead and try. Just hope you don't die too soon from my radiation.

312
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:10,533
MC: Just like right now, you've been around me without any protection for too long.

313
00:28:10,533 --> 00:28:22,000
In this gamble, that ever-surging power now settles in my heart. It feels unfamiliar to me, yet at this moment, it seems to belong to me completely.

314
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:28,933
His deep eyes fill with more laughter. He elegantly sets the machine aside, squats down, and places his hands on both sides of the bag.

315
00:28:28,933 --> 00:28:37,000
His warm breath hits my face, and he seems like another cage, closing in on me even more.

316
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:55,400
Lucien: Do you know? Ten years ago, your data readings fluctuated wildly. They thought it was due to your unstable condition, but I suspected back then that it was because of ‘fear’.

317
00:28:55,400 --> 00:29:11,166
Lucien: Humans can feel the existence of life through extreme fear. They will instinctively want to protect themselves, and that drive will generate immense energy.

318
00:29:11,166 --> 00:29:28,666
Lucien: Back then, my knowledge and skills were far from sufficient to fully uncover everything about you, so I concluded... that we both needed some time.

319
00:29:28,666 --> 00:29:41,200
Lucien: [whispers] But later, I regretted it. Actually, I shouldn't have let you go back then.

320
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:46,466
His gentle voice brushes past my ear like a feather, making me instinctively hold my breath.

321
00:29:46,466 --> 00:29:51,633
Something heavy and complex seems to be shedding its outer shell, revealing a more genuine and indescribable side to me.

322
00:29:51,633 --> 00:30:01,733
Lucien: A lot of time was wasted, so when you appeared before me, I was very happy.

323
00:30:01,733 --> 00:30:09,033
Lucien: And you're slowly starting to trust me, which is good.

324
00:30:09,033 --> 00:30:13,933
MC: So everything over the past six months... was it all your facade?

325
00:30:13,933 --> 00:30:18,600
MC: To make me truly feel fear?

326
00:30:18,600 --> 00:30:31,466
Lucien: No, I want you to always remember the feeling you just had.

327
00:30:31,466 --> 00:30:38,200
His noticeably cold fingertips brush my cheek, meticulously tracing a certain outline.

328
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:50,366
Lucien: You should have been constantly thinking, striving to survive, and seeing many scenes.

329
00:30:50,366 --> 00:30:58,166
Lucien: Remember how you used that power and then tame it.

330
00:30:58,166 --> 00:31:04,700
Lucien: Only then will you be complete.

331
00:31:04,700 --> 00:31:09,200
A pair of calm abysses engulf me, tempting me to gaze upon what lies hidden deep beneath the surface-

332
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:13,866
A soul that is pure yet obsessive, mad yet patient.

333
00:31:13,866 --> 00:31:23,000
Lucien: Besides, I have never pretended in front of you. Just because you don’t see it doesn't mean it doesn't exist.

334
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:33,466
Lucien: Our time is running out. I think it's a good idea to use myself as a stepping stone for change.

335
00:31:33,466 --> 00:31:44,666
Lucien: After all, solving the problem is the key to everything, and I don't want to cause you too much pain.

336
00:31:44,666 --> 00:31:49,866
I freeze momentarily, suddenly realizing something, and repeatedly examine his entire body.

337
00:31:49,866 --> 00:31:56,633
The person in front of me has no skin ulcers, looks mentally stable, and everything seems normal…

338
00:31:56,633 --> 00:32:00,700
MC: Could it be that you…

339
00:32:00,700 --> 00:32:08,633
Lucien: I am my own test subject, and the facts prove that I have succeeded.

340
00:32:08,633 --> 00:32:13,466
He lifts his palm, revealing faint flickering motes of light. I can sense a power radiating from within.

341
00:32:13,466 --> 00:32:21,200
Lucien: As I've mentioned before, your body seems to possess a sort of 'core' or 'field'.

342
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:32,400
Lucien: Your core affects the radiation energy, either absorbing or repelling it; hence, you remain unaffected.

343
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:41,200
Lucien: And I used the power you unleashed earlier to replicate a similar 'field'.

344
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:45,433
Flecks of excitement dance in his eyes as he arrogantly retracts his fingertips.

345
00:32:45,433 --> 00:32:59,700
Lucien: [chuckles] If my hypothesis is correct, in a few days, I will be able to create a 'core' with a near-identical operating mechanism in a few days.

346
00:32:59,700 --> 00:33:11,300
Lucien: I might soon be able to research the data from the heavily contaminated areas myself, including... the machines there.

347
00:33:11,300 --> 00:33:17,366
With that, he rises to his feet, carefully placing various organs and components into separate jars before turning his head back.

348
00:33:17,366 --> 00:33:27,266
Lucien: I previously asked you, 'Is death the end?' Do you remember your answer?

349
00:33:27,266 --> 00:33:31,766
MC: ...I remember.

350
00:33:31,766 --> 00:33:37,766
Lucien: I don't think death is the end.

351
00:33:37,766 --> 00:33:41,666
He lets out a soft chuckle tinged with an air of undeniable arrogance.

352
00:33:41,666 --> 00:33:55,400
Lucien: No one here cares about death, because it's too commonplace, and also because they don't understand the value of death.

353
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:59,966
Watching his retreating figure without turning his head, I instinctively crawl out of the black bag.

354
00:33:59,966 --> 00:34:04,133
I feel as if I've just experienced death and have been reborn with new flesh and blood in this moment.

355
00:34:04,133 --> 00:34:09,000
I want to know what he means and see how far he can go.

356
00:34:10,233 --> 00:34:16,900
Following his figure, I enter a room on the side of the deep pit. Jars of all shapes and sizes are placed in the dimly lit environment.

357
00:34:16,900 --> 00:34:22,266
The wall is covered with a dense jumble of numbers and changing curves, new numbers and symbols overlapping the old marks, layer upon layer.

358
00:34:22,266 --> 00:34:26,233
I look around in surprise, momentarily at a loss for words.

359
00:34:26,233 --> 00:34:29,600
MC: These... are all your doing?

360
00:34:29,600 --> 00:34:36,033
Lucien: Not entirely, I just took over them.

361
00:34:36,033 --> 00:34:40,466
He places the jars on different shelves and writes new numbers in one spot.

362
00:34:40,466 --> 00:34:54,266
Lucien: Someone else conducted experiments here before, leaving behind many things and data. There are always predecessors doing similar things, just like the information you brought back.

363
00:34:54,266 --> 00:35:04,500
Lucien: I just found them, researched and revised their conclusions, and came up with my own answers.

364
00:35:04,500 --> 00:35:07,833
MC: How do you know that someone else will do the same thing…?

365
00:35:07,833 --> 00:35:11,566
Lucien: There will always be.

366
00:35:11,566 --> 00:35:22,466
Lucien: There will always be those who are curious, questioning all the current definitions and conjectures, wanting to know how this world actually works.

367
00:35:22,466 --> 00:35:33,666
Lucien: There are always things that spread wider and longer than diseases and death, leaving their mark on the world in various ways.

368
00:35:33,666 --> 00:35:37,700
I stand there in a daze, Lucien is clearly standing in front of me, yet I feel like he is so far away.

369
00:35:37,700 --> 00:35:43,000
In a world ravaged by wounds, his words sounded like a miracle, but he spoke them as if it were a matter of course.

370
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:48,266
At this moment, I suddenly have a premonition.

371
00:35:48,266 --> 00:35:56,500
Even if Lucien disappears from the world one day, there will surely be someone who will sweep away the dust of time, pick up the whole box, and continue to climb upwards on this silent boulder.

372
00:35:56,500 --> 00:36:03,466
Lucien: Aside from that, these corpses are also quite nutritious.

373
00:36:03,466 --> 00:36:10,433
Having seemingly finished his preparations, Lucien spoke abruptly, causing my expression to change instantly.

374
00:36:11,733 --> 00:36:16,033
Following his footsteps, I arrive at another dark, large building. I had never thought that the buildings next to the laboratory each had their own purpose.

375
00:36:16,033 --> 00:36:24,033
Amidst the continuous rumbling, Lucien opens each black bag one by one and empties their contents into a deep pit, its contents and depth obscured from view.

376
00:36:24,033 --> 00:36:32,833
Lucien: Corpses can be fermented by bacteria to produce biogas, which is a tremendous source of chemical energy.

377
00:36:32,833 --> 00:36:42,466
Lucien: Moreover, improper handling of these corpses could lead to an outbreak of plague, resulting in even more deaths.

378
00:36:42,466 --> 00:36:47,866
Unable to understand what he's saying, I stare into the depths of the pit for a long moment before turning my gaze towards Lucien.

379
00:36:47,866 --> 00:36:51,900
MC: Have you been experimenting on the people in the city all this time?

380
00:36:51,900 --> 00:36:58,000
Lucien: I don't deny it.

381
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:06,133
Faced with his somewhat ambiguous answer, I fall silent for a moment.

382
00:37:06,133 --> 00:37:16,833
Lucien is both saving and experimenting. It seems as if the divine and the devil coexist paradoxically within him, making it impossible for me to define him in any way.

383
00:37:16,833 --> 00:37:23,633
Lucien: The more people who survive, the more it proves that my path is the correct one.

384
00:37:23,633 --> 00:37:34,233
Lucien: I deeply regret the loss of those who died, but I will only use their deaths to go further.

385
00:37:35,633 --> 00:37:39,100
As we leave the building, the sky is so dark that no single star can be seen.

386
00:37:41,366 --> 00:37:46,633
Lucien doesn't stop but walks towards the city.

387
00:37:46,633 --> 00:37:54,066
Seeing this, I instinctively halt—I am not wearing my isolation suit, and my presence could harm the city's residents.

388
00:37:54,066 --> 00:37:59,200
Lucien: It's okay, MC. Trust me.

389
00:37:59,200 --> 00:38:02,900
He stands in the darkness yet extends an invitation to me like a burning flame.

390
00:38:02,900 --> 00:38:09,866
Lucien: Let me show you what this world can be.

391
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:17,000
In the empty square, not a sliver of light is visible. Lucien takes out a small device, instantly illuminating his face. A small, dome-shaped black hole is also aimed at me.

392
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:19,133
MC: …!

393
00:38:19,133 --> 00:38:23,100
Instinctively assuming it to be a weapon, I cover my neck and recoil half a step.

394
00:38:23,100 --> 00:38:28,666
Unexpectedly, Lucien laughs and gestures with the device at me for quite a while. I instinctively try to escape his ‘target lock’, but it only makes his laughter more pronounced.

395
00:38:28,666 --> 00:38:33,933
Finally, I can't resist moving closer. After he presses the button, I find myself appearing on the lit-up screen!

396
00:38:33,933 --> 00:38:39,766
The me in the picture frame steps back in fear, nervously runs around, and finally moves closer out of curiosity.

397
00:38:39,766 --> 00:38:41,800
MC: …What is this! So amazing!

398
00:38:41,800 --> 00:38:51,400
Lucien: I don't know either. But since we've found it, it means someone invented it in this world.

399
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:58,266
Lucien: It has no significance for survival, yet it still exists.

400
00:38:58,266 --> 00:39:02,966
With a gentle shake of the device, specks of light dance exuberantly in his eyes.

401
00:39:02,966 --> 00:39:10,466
Lucien: How boring it would be if the only meaning of this world was survival.

402
00:39:10,466 --> 00:39:14,200
My heart is racing, and the moment I take the device, it feels heavy.

403
00:39:14,200 --> 00:39:17,733
I don't know what I pressed, but Lucien's face appears on the screen.

404
00:39:17,733 --> 00:39:21,533
Lucien looks straight at me through the device.

405
00:39:21,533 --> 00:39:34,533
Lucien: [softly] MC, do you know? From the moment you appeared before me, I realized that this world is actually full of color.

406
00:39:34,533 --> 00:39:45,900
Lucien: So, I really want you to see what the world looks like through my eyes.

407
00:39:45,900 --> 00:39:50,933
An unknown button press triggers a blinding flash of light that erupts in an instant, searing an imprint onto my retinas-

408
00:39:50,933 --> 00:39:55,833
The whole world seems to be glowing.

409
00:39:55,833 --> 00:40:04,333
Multicolored luminescence suffuses every corner of the city. The splendid and brilliant lights are like eternal fireworks, blooming with unparalleled beauty.

410
00:40:04,333 --> 00:40:07,166
Zone X is lit up.

411
00:40:07,166 --> 00:40:11,833
Shadowy figures emerge from the corners, their heads raised and eyes wide open.

412
00:40:11,833 --> 00:40:13,900
??: ...Is this also a radiation tide?

413
00:40:13,900 --> 00:40:18,900
??: It must be... it must be! Run! Otherwise, none of us will survive!

414
00:40:18,900 --> 00:40:22,133
??: It hurts! I feel so much pain!!

415
00:40:22,133 --> 00:40:25,033
??: Wait… City lord is over there!

416
00:40:25,033 --> 00:40:28,533
??: City lord! Save us!!

417
00:40:28,533 --> 00:40:35,733
Countless cries of clamor and anguish rise and fall, eyes full of pleading and struggle are cast in my direction.

418
00:40:35,733 --> 00:40:42,033
Lucien: These are all my doing, they are just some lights that I turned on.

419
00:40:42,033 --> 00:40:46,533
As those words settle, the entire square instantly falls silent.

420
00:40:46,533 --> 00:40:50,366
??: There's no way so many lights would turn on in this world... you must be lying!

421
00:40:50,366 --> 00:40:53,500
??: ...Really? Could it be that City Lord is just that powerful?

422
00:40:53,500 --> 00:40:55,600
??: Run!!

423
00:40:55,600 --> 00:41:00,233
In that fleeting moment, I seem to perceive a myriad of faces. Doubt, curiosity, anger, despair...

424
00:41:00,233 --> 00:41:05,666
In the unfamiliar yet radiant scene of rebirth, something sprouts and grows amidst the ruins.

425
00:41:05,666 --> 00:41:12,066
As someone charges forward with a roar, Lucien remains nonchalant, a smile still gracing his lips.

426
00:41:12,066 --> 00:41:15,866
His eyes hold no trace of them.

427
00:41:15,866 --> 00:41:28,066
Lucien: MC, the future awaiting everyone will never be peaceful; death and struggle will inevitably permeate the entirety of human history.

428
00:41:28,066 --> 00:41:42,133
Lucien: But if, after enduring pain and struggle, one can gain the courage to face the truth, it will surely lead humanity to a further future.

429
00:41:42,133 --> 00:41:45,666
MC: ...What kind of future?

430
00:41:45,666 --> 00:41:48,700
Lucien: For example…

431
00:41:48,700 --> 00:41:53,900
As blood splatters everywhere, I see Lucien proudly raise the corners of his mouth.

432
00:41:53,900 --> 00:42:00,900
Lucien: You can stand in front of everyone just as ordinarily as this.

433
00:42:00,900 --> 00:42:06,300
Lucien: Without restrictions, in a state of freedom.

434
00:42:06,300 --> 00:42:12,800
Lucien: I think this future is just beginning.

435
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:19,966
Lucien extends his hand to me as he speaks.

436
00:42:19,966 --> 00:42:27,300
I have never seen someone like this, standing before me in such a real and equal way, in the face of me who always brings death to others because of my radiation.

437
00:42:27,300 --> 00:42:35,266
He has calculated everything and cut open everything, inviting me to embark on an unknown and long journey together.

438
00:42:35,266 --> 00:42:40,366
Almost without hesitation, I step forward and grasp that hand, letting the blood stains on it also stain my hand.

439
00:42:40,366 --> 00:42:45,033
Since he has used himself and the future as bait, then I have absolutely no reason to give up.

440
00:42:45,033 --> 00:42:49,000
MC: Lucien, is all of this tonight part of your bigger trap?

441
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:53,833
Lucien: [chuckles] What if it is?

442
00:42:53,833 --> 00:42:58,200
I stare back at him deeply, the corners of my mouth curling into a smile.

443
00:42:58,200 --> 00:43:02,100
MC: Then I will gladly accept it.

444
00:43:02,100 --> 00:43:07,666
With a dazzling halo around his arched eyebrows and eyes, he pulls my hand up and we start running together.

445
00:43:07,666 --> 00:43:17,833
Lucien: The isolation membrane I placed on you only lasts for 15 minutes. "Miss Death" is about to come again.

446
00:43:17,833 --> 00:43:23,566
As he speaks, he spreads his palm open with a serious demeanor. Despite being covered in blood, he appears as graceful as the wisest grand wizard from a book.

447
00:43:23,566 --> 00:43:29,166
I can't help but laugh, placing my hand in his as if placing both my life and death in his hand.

448
00:43:29,166 --> 00:43:31,666
MC: Pfft, don't you need to escape from me then?

449
00:43:31,666 --> 00:43:34,300
Lucien: I don't need to.

450
00:43:34,300 --> 00:43:35,833
He laughs casually, and there’s even a hint of anticipation.

451
00:43:35,833 --> 00:43:39,233
Lucien: Death is one of my best nutrients.

452
00:43:39,233 --> 00:43:42,533
The static dark screens served as a backdrop behind him. The neon light outlines his silhouette as if it could illuminate everything.

453
00:43:42,533 --> 00:43:45,566
I subconsciously raise the device in my hand and aim it behind us-

454
00:43:45,566 --> 00:43:48,466
Countless images of Lucien appear on the machines behind me. I excitedly sway it back and forth, and the pictures of the machine sway in real time along with my movements.

455
00:43:48,466 --> 00:43:50,800
MC: You need to tell me what's happening when you return!

456
00:43:50,800 --> 00:43:53,966
Lucien: I'd be happy to explain it to you.

457
00:43:53,966 --> 00:43:55,600
MC: Then I also want to know the principle behind it and more!

458
00:43:55,600 --> 00:44:00,666
Lucien: In that case, a certain student might need to put in a bit more effort outside of the experiments.

459
00:44:00,666 --> 00:44:03,033
The sky starts to rain at some point, as if a joyful symphony is playing.

460
00:44:03,033 --> 00:44:05,200
MC: Lucien, do you find this world interesting?

461
00:44:05,200 --> 00:44:09,566
Lucien: Incredibly interesting.

462
00:44:09,566 --> 00:44:12,133
MC: I'm starting to find it interesting too!

463
00:44:12,133 --> 00:44:15,166
I've never felt so free and happy. All the unknowns seem to have transformed into challenges at this moment, and I want to overcome them.

464
00:44:15,166 --> 00:44:17,566
MC: With Zone X being so bright, more people are bound to notice it, right?

465
00:44:17,566 --> 00:44:25,833
Lucien: Probably, similar people will understand its significance. Some will come closer, and some will question it—

466
00:44:25,833 --> 00:44:32,533
Lucien: But perhaps more and more areas will light up like this.

467
00:44:32,533 --> 00:44:40,266
Lucien: The data you brought back contains a very special piece of information.

468
00:44:40,266 --> 00:44:51,800
Lucien: It is said that there is a person in this world who can change everything. The recorder referred to her as — 'Queen'.

469
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:53,900
I was stunned for a moment and slowly stopped walking.

470
00:44:53,900 --> 00:44:57,266
Lucien stands in front of me, still gazing at me with a gentle smile.

471
00:44:57,266 --> 00:45:00,733
I look at our intertwined palms, and after a long while, I raise my head resolutely and hold his hand even tighter.

472
00:45:00,733 --> 00:45:03,666
MC: If there really is someone who can change everything, I will be that person.

473
00:45:03,666 --> 00:45:06,633
MC: I will be the 'Queen'.

474
00:45:06,633 --> 00:45:10,433
Lucien smiles gently.

475
00:45:10,433 --> 00:45:16,100
Lucien: Then I will witness your coronation.

476
00:45:16,100 --> 00:45:20,933
He holds my hand, steps over the line between light and darkness, and merges into the darkness.

477
00:45:20,933 --> 00:45:27,533
Lucien: Welcome to the new world.

478
00:45:27,533 --> 00:45:31,533
Thank you for reading! I put my thoughts about the date in the comment if you are interested in that :)